11/02/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- US Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Thomas Countryman was in Skopje on Thursday (February 10th) talking to Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski about Washington's concerns regarding the state of the judiciary and media freedom in Macedonia. 
Countryman also welcomed recent meetings between Greek and Macedonian officials in ongoing efforts to resolve the bilateral name dispute. 
Countryman met with Branko Crvenkovski, leader of the main opposition SDSM, about the parliamentary boycott the SDSM is staging and about Skopje's EU integration process. 
Countryman heads next to Pristina. 
(BBC Macedonian, A1, Kirilica, Vecer - 10/02/11)
